claim.claim-text:
17. A method to adjust a duty cycle of an output clock signal, the method comprising:
generating an output clock signal based upon an input clock signal, wherein a duty cycle of the output clock signal is based upon a delay signal;
oscillating with frequencies dependent upon high and low states of the output clock signal to generate a first detector signal, wherein oscillating with frequencies dependent upon high and low states of the output clock signal comprises varying a current available to an oscillator based upon a voltage level of the output clock signal;
oscillating with frequencies dependent upon high and low states of an inverted output clock signal to generate a second detector signal;
comparing averages of the frequencies of the detector signals; and
generating the delay signal based upon the comparison.
